snippet: Queen Elizabeth II wound up a spectacular and closely scripted four-day celebration of her 60 years as monarch on Tuesday, seeming buoyed by an outpouring of support.
abstract: Queen Elizabeth II concludes her jubilee celebration with a nationally-broadcasted address, expressing gratitude and humility for the spectacular outpouring of support by her subjects.

byline.original: By ALAN COWELL and JOHN F. BURNS
